args: What follows is the record of an incident that\noccurred on the eve of Nobunaga's journey to\nsouthern Grastaea.
The disappearances have started\nhappening in our territory as well...\nThis is a true crisis!
So a merchant couple has disappeared...\nAnd in your territory, too.
Yep. It's happening in your domain too,\nisn't it, Nobunaga?

Indeed. In the span of a single night,
the whole of a samurai household was
spirited away...and their whereabouts
remain unknown.
It's a real humdinger of a mystery. Given\nmy position, I've got to do SOMETHING.\nI just don't know what.
You're going to pitch in on this,\nright, Nobunaga?
Did you not call me here for the express\npurpose of soliciting my aid? No need to\nplay innocent at this point.
Hah, you know me so well! Now, let's get\nthis mystery-solving show on the road!
Trust that I never act in half-measures.\nI will slice right to the heart of this case!
Go, go! I'll watch you from back here\nand let you know if I notice anything.
Heh. Of course. I charge onward,\neyes fixed firmly on the road ahead!
You know, for a layabout and a hot-\nblooded meathead, you two make one heck\nof a team! I can really tell you're old pals.
With you on the case, this mystery is\nas good as solved! Isn't that right,\nDaikokuten—wait, Daikokuten?
Daikokuten? What is it, boy? Speak!
I'm no bloodhound! Anyway, this pillar is\npositively swathed in the most divine scent\nof Amaterasu!
Curious... Could she have passed through\nhere?
Oh! Could Amaterasu herself be trying to\nout-sleuth us and resolve the mystery?!

She ushered in the end of a turbulent era
and built a world of peace. With power like
that, I bet she could find these missing
people without breaking a sweat!
It's possible, but it would be strange for\nher to have arrived here without word of\nher visit making it to me.
The idea of someone of her stature\ntraveling incognito certainly is unusual.\nAre you certain the scent belongs to her?
If I could just get a little nibble of this\npillar here, I'd know quite conclusively...\n*nibble nibble*
Daikokuten, you're gonna chip a tooth!\n...Aaand he's not listening.
Mm, yes indeed! This scent—this flavor!\nIt is unmistakably Amaterasu's!
Wh-what's going on?! The light is\ngrowing stronger and stronger!
Bad vibes, bad vibes! BOOK IT,\nmy lady! Nobuna—
It happened right after Daikokuten bit the\npillar. Could the two be related?
And it sounded like Chitose got cut off\nwhile he was speaking.
What? So he truly is gone. Or at the very\nleast, not near us any longer...
He disappeared like so much smoke!\nWas he spirited away?!
Chitose, answer me! This game of hide-\nand-seek is no fun anymore!
Calm yourself, Mitsuhide! Your distress\nis understandable, but right now, we need\nto—
How can I possibly be calm?! No one who's\ndisappeared has come back!
Chitose may be a goofball, but he's also\nmy precious retainer! He can't be gone!

Compose yourself! You are a leader, and
for you to lose your wits in full view of
your subjects will do naught but...bring
them...unease...
Was the castle town always this quiet?\nWe appear to be utterly alone.
...You're right. There's no one here.\nWhat's going on?
Not just people, but dogs and cats and\nbirds too! There's no sign of any animals!
I am loath to believe this, but judging\nfrom the situation...
I believe the ones who disappeared...\nMight have been us!
